cohort.memory: During my first Group Project on Server-Side I got stuck trying to push one get-all function to github.  It was as if I was stuck in some sort of GitMaze (which doesn't exist).  So I'm pushing up this function up all week it seems (which works for me) and finally got approval to merge. Immediately I move on to other things and implement Client-Side features.  At the end of the week everything looked fine and the beginning of the following I open up GitHub and there it is...My unmerged code.  What?  How?  How embarrassing...right?  I create another pull request and label it Pull Request of Shame...  How about them apples.
